quote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">U.S. Senator Marco Rubio (R-FL) introduc=
ed the Mind Your Own Business Act, which would enable shareholders to hold =
woke corporations accountable. Specifically, the legislation would require =
corporate directors to prove their =E2=80=9Cwoke=E2=80=9D corporate actions=
 were in their shareholders=E2=80=99 best interest in order to avoid liabil=
ity for breach of fiduciary duty in shareholder litigation over corporate a=
ctions relating to certain social policies. It would also incentivize corpo=
rate management to stop abusing their positions to advance left-wing social=
 policies by increasing their personal liability to shareholders for breach=
es of fiduciary duty resulting from those policies. Rubio announced the bil=
l during an appearance with Maria Bartiromo on Mornings with Maria and in a=
 Fox Business op-ed. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CNo =
more legal tricks that shield these corporate executives from accountabilit=
y,=E2=80=9D Rubio continued. =E2=80=9CIf they really believe that being wok=
e is good for business, they should have to say so=E2=80=94and prove it=E2=
=80=94under oath in court.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Rubio=
=E2=80=99s Mind Your Own Business Act is a private-sector solution to the p=
roblem of woke corporations. Specifically the bill:=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Requires large public companies listing on national stock ex=
changes to provide shareholders with significant holdings with certain priv=
ileges with respect to claims for breach of fiduciary duty under covered ci=
